{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MQvEK3vW8nbeASxm6nNmNn","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nPerformed adversarial code review on story 0-5-3 (Ink Terminal Renderer). Found and fixed 3 issues:\n\n**Fixed:**\n1. **HIGH — Unused `STATUS_SYMBOLS` constant** (`ink-components.tsx`): The constant was defined but symbols were hardcoded inline in `StoryBreakdown`. Refactored to use `STATUS_SYMBOLS` via a `fmt()` helper, eliminating the maintenance divergence risk.\n2. **MEDIUM — No defensive copy in `updateStories()`** (`ink-renderer.tsx`): Changed `state.stories = stories` to `state.stories = [...stories]` to prevent caller mutation from corrupting renderer state.\n3. **HIGH — Missing test coverage for new methods after cleanup** (`ink-renderer.test.tsx`): Added `updateStories()` and `addMessage()` calls to the \"ignores updates after cleanup\" test. Also added signal handler tests (SIGINT/SIGTERM) and a MAX_COMPLETED_TOOLS bounds test.\n\n**Results:**\n- 50 tests pass (was 47), 2679 total tests pass\n- `ink-components.tsx`: 100% all metrics\n- `ink-renderer.tsx`: 100% lines, 100% functions, 100% statements, 96.77% branches\n- `codeharness coverage --min-file 80`: all 110 files above 80%, overall 96.53%\n- Story status updated to `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: `STATUS_SYMBOLS` constant defined but unused — symbols were hardcoded inline, creating divergence risk. Fixed.\n- HIGH: `updateStories()` and `addMessage()` post-cleanup guard (`if (cleaned) return;`) untested. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: `updateStories()` took caller's array reference without defensive copy — caller mutation could corrupt renderer state. Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- LOW: `truncateToWidth()` is a private function that can't be unit-tested independently. It's covered through `LastThought` component tests, but a dedicated export + test would allow more granular edge-case testing (e.g., maxWidth=0, empty string, mixed ASCII/CJK).\n- LOW: `rerender()` has a defensive `if (!cleaned)` guard (line 89) that is unreachable in normal code flow because all callers already check `cleaned`. The false branch is technically dead code but harmless as a safety net. Branch coverage at 96.77% because of this.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- `ink-renderer.tsx` branch coverage at 96.77% — the unreachable `rerender()` guard false branch (line 89). Not practically testable without violating encapsulation.\n- No integration tests verifying the actual rendered output matches the UX spec format end-to-end (component tests verify content, not exact layout/ordering in pixel-perfect sense). This is expected — Story 0.5.4 handles integration with `run.ts`.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The component/controller split is clean. Types are well-defined. State management is correct (immutable updates, shallow copy for rerender).\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Coverage passes."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2f57c4b261377af4 (use SendMessage with to: 'a2f57c4b261377af4' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 46776\ntool_uses: 30\nduration_ms: 188398</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1eada203-6dd0-4cf1-909a-4daaca264b98","uuid":"bd06b680-74cc-4045-a7ec-bbd39729d3b4","timestamp":"2026-03-20T07:15:13.573Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/0-5-3-ink-terminal-renderer.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"a2f57c4b261377af4","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nPerformed adversarial code review on story 0-5-3 (Ink Terminal Renderer). Found and fixed 3 issues:\n\n**Fixed:**\n1. **HIGH — Unused `STATUS_SYMBOLS` constant** (`ink-components.tsx`): The constant was defined but symbols were hardcoded inline in `StoryBreakdown`. Refactored to use `STATUS_SYMBOLS` via a `fmt()` helper, eliminating the maintenance divergence risk.\n2. **MEDIUM — No defensive copy in `updateStories()`** (`ink-renderer.tsx`): Changed `state.stories = stories` to `state.stories = [...stories]` to prevent caller mutation from corrupting renderer state.\n3. **HIGH — Missing test coverage for new methods after cleanup** (`ink-renderer.test.tsx`): Added `updateStories()` and `addMessage()` calls to the \"ignores updates after cleanup\" test. Also added signal handler tests (SIGINT/SIGTERM) and a MAX_COMPLETED_TOOLS bounds test.\n\n**Results:**\n- 50 tests pass (was 47), 2679 total tests pass\n- `ink-components.tsx`: 100% all metrics\n- `ink-renderer.tsx`: 100% lines, 100% functions, 100% statements, 96.77% branches\n- `codeharness coverage --min-file 80`: all 110 files above 80%, overall 96.53%\n- Story status updated to `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: `STATUS_SYMBOLS` constant defined but unused — symbols were hardcoded inline, creating divergence risk. Fixed.\n- HIGH: `updateStories()` and `addMessage()` post-cleanup guard (`if (cleaned) return;`) untested. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: `updateStories()` took caller's array reference without defensive copy — caller mutation could corrupt renderer state. Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- LOW: `truncateToWidth()` is a private function that can't be unit-tested independently. It's covered through `LastThought` component tests, but a dedicated export + test would allow more granular edge-case testing (e.g., maxWidth=0, empty string, mixed ASCII/CJK).\n- LOW: `rerender()` has a defensive `if (!cleaned)` guard (line 89) that is unreachable in normal code flow because all callers already check `cleaned`. The false branch is technically dead code but harmless as a safety net. Branch coverage at 96.77% because of this.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- `ink-renderer.tsx` branch coverage at 96.77% — the unreachable `rerender()` guard false branch (line 89). Not practically testable without violating encapsulation.\n- No integration tests verifying the actual rendered output matches the UX spec format end-to-end (component tests verify content, not exact layout/ordering in pixel-perfect sense). This is expected — Story 0.5.4 handles integration with `run.ts`.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The component/controller split is clean. Types are well-defined. State management is correct (immutable updates, shallow copy for rerender).\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Coverage passes."}],"totalDurationMs":188398,"totalTokens":46776,"totalToolUseCount":30,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":247,"cache_read_input_tokens":45752,"output_tokens":776,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":247},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
