{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JRFoGBN13cRjgbffgT2YdA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 0.5.3: Ink Terminal Renderer\n     2→\n     3→Status: verifying\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As an operator,\n     8→I want a rich terminal UI built with Ink that shows live Claude activity, per-story progress, session timing, and story completion messages,\n     9→so that I can see at a glance what Claude is doing, how the sprint is progressing, and what happened to each story.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→1. **Given** Claude is executing tools during a run, **When** the operator watches the terminal, **Then** they see the active tool with a spinner (`⚡ [ToolName]`) and each completed tool as a permanent line (`✓ [ToolName] args...`). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→\n    15→2. **Given** Claude is producing text output, **When** the operator watches the terminal, **Then** they see the latest thought on an updating line (`💭 {text}`), truncated to terminal width. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→\n    17→3. **Given** a running session, **When** the Ink header renders, **Then** it shows the current story key, phase, elapsed time, and sprint progress — matching the UX spec format: `◆ {story_key} — {phase} | {elapsed} | Sprint: {done}/{total}`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→\n    19→4. **Given** sprint state data with per-story statuses, **When** the renderer displays the story breakdown section, **Then** it shows stories grouped by status using the UX spec symbols: `✓` done, `◆` in-progress, `○` pending, `✗` failed, `✕` blocked/exhausted — e.g. `Done: 3-1 ✓  4-1 ✓  4-2 ✓ | This: 3-2 ◆ | Next: 3-3 ○`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→\n    21→5. **Given** a story completes verification successfully, **When** the renderer receives a story-complete event, **Then** it displays `[OK] Story {key}: DONE — {AC count} ACs verified` with duration and cost on a subsequent line. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→\n    23→6. **Given** a story fails verification, **When** the renderer receives a story-failed event, **Then** it displays `[WARN] Story {key}: verification found {N} failing ACs → returning to dev` with the failing AC details and attempt count. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→\n    25→7. **Given** an API retry event, **When** rendered, **Then** it shows `⏳ API retry {attempt} (waiting {delay}ms)`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    26→\n    27→8. **Given** the `--quiet` flag is set, **When** the renderer is started, **Then** no terminal output is produced — a no-op handle is returned. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    28→\n    29→9. **Given** process exit (SIGINT, SIGTERM, or natural end), **When** Ink cleans up, **Then** no orphaned terminal state (cursor, alternate screen buffer) remains. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    30→\n    31→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    32→\n    33→- [x] Task 1: Expand SprintInfo type and Header component (AC: #3)\n    34→  - [x] Add `elapsed?: string` to SprintInfo\n    35→  - [x] Update Header to render elapsed time: `◆ {storyKey} — {phase} | {elapsed} | Sprint: {done}/{total}`\n    36→  - [x] Update tests for new header format\n    37→\n    38→- [x] Task 2: Add per-story status breakdown component (AC: #4)\n    39→  - [x] Define `StoryStatusEntry` type: `{ key: string; status: StoryStatusValue }`\n    40→  - [x] Add `stories: StoryStatusEntry[]` to RendererState\n    41→  - [x] Create `StoryBreakdown` component that groups stories by status and renders with correct symbols (✓/◆/○/✗/✕)\n    42→  - [x] Add `updateStories(stories: StoryStatusEntry[])` to RendererHandle\n    43→  - [x] Compact single-line format: `Done: 3-1 ✓  4-1 ✓ | This: 3-2 ◆ | Next: 3-3 ○`\n    44→  - [x] Update tests\n    45→\n    46→- [x] Task 3: Add story completion/failure message components (AC: #5, #6)\n    47→  - [x] Define `StoryMessage` type: `{ type: 'ok' | 'warn' | 'fail'; key: string; message: string; details?: string[] }`\n    48→  - [x] Add `messages: StoryMessage[]` to RendererState\n    49→  - [x] Create `StoryMessages` component rendering `[OK]`/`[WARN]`/`[FAIL]` lines per UX spec format\n    50→  - [x] Add `addMessage(msg: StoryMessage)` to RendererHandle\n    51→  - [x] Messages are permanent (append-only, not overwritten)\n    52→  - [x] Update tests\n    53→\n    54→- [x] Task 4: Wire new components into App and renderer controller (AC: #1-#9)\n    55→  - [x] Add StoryBreakdown and StoryMessages to App component tree\n    56→  - [x] Expose new methods on RendererHandle: `updateStories()`, `addMessage()`\n    57→  - [x] Ensure no-op handle includes new methods\n    58→  - [x] Verify signal handling still works with expanded state\n    59→\n    60→- [x] Task 5: Update tests for all new/changed behavior (AC: #1-#9)\n    61→  - [x] Test Header renders elapsed time\n    62→  - [x] Test StoryBreakdown renders correct symbols per status\n    63→  - [x] Test StoryMessages renders [OK], [WARN], [FAIL] formats\n    64→  - [x] Test updateStories() and addMessage() on RendererHandle\n    65→  - [x] Test no-op handle includes new methods\n    66→  - [x] All 29 existing tests still pass (47 total now)\n    67→\n    68→## Dev Notes\n    69→\n    70→### What Exists (Enhance, Don't Rewrite)\n    71→\n    72→The Ink renderer already works for tool activity display. This story ENHANCES it with:\n    73→1. Richer header (add elapsed time)\n    74→2. Per-story status section (new component)\n    75→3. Story completion messages (new component)\n    76→\n    77→**Do NOT rewrite ink-components.tsx or ink-renderer.tsx from scratch.** Add new components and expand existing types. The existing tool activity display (⚡ spinner, ✓ completed, 💭 thought, ⏳ retry) is correct and should not change.\n    78→\n    79→### Key Files to Modify\n    80→\n    81→- `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` — Add StoryBreakdown, StoryMessages components; expand SprintInfo type; update Header; update App\n    82→- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` — Expand RendererState; add updateStories(), addMessage() to handle; update no-op handle\n    83→- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` — Add tests for new components and API\n    84→\n    85→### Key Files to Read (Do NOT Modify)\n    86→\n    87→- `src/lib/stream-parser.ts` — StreamEvent types consumed by the renderer\n    88→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Where the renderer is integrated (modified in 0.5.4, not this story)\n    89→\n    90→### Architecture Constraints\n    91→\n    92→- **NFR9: No file > 300 lines.** If ink-components.tsx exceeds 300 lines after adding new components, split into `ink-components.tsx` (existing) and `ink-status-components.tsx` (new story/status components).\n    93→- **Vitest** for unit tests, **100% coverage target**\n    94→- **ink-testing-library** for component rendering tests (already a devDependency)\n    95→- **TSX** with `\"jsx\": \"react-jsx\"` in tsconfig (already configured)\n    96→\n    97→### UX Spec Reference — Expected Visual Output\n    98→\n    99→The live mode display should look like this (from UX spec):\n   100→\n   101→```\n   102→◆ 3-2-bmad-installation-workflow-patching — verify | 47m | Sprint: 18/65\n   103→Done: 3-1 ✓  4-1 ✓  4-2 ✓\n   104→This: 3-2 ◆ verifying\n   105→Next: 3-3 ○\n   106→\n   107→✓ [Bash] npm run test:unit 2>&1 | tail -20\n   108→✓ [Read] src/modules/sprint/state.ts\n   109→⚡ [Bash] docker exec codeharness-verify ...\n   110→💭 Running the verification container to check AC 8...\n   111→```\n   112→\n   113→Story completion messages (displayed between stories):\n   114→```\n   115→[OK] Story 3-2: DONE — 12/12 ACs verified (18m, $4.20)\n   116→[WARN] Story 3-3: verification found 2 failing ACs → returning to dev (attempt 2/10)\n   117→```\n   118→\n   119→### Previous Story Intelligence (0.5.2)\n   120→\n   121→- Parser is stateless per-line; renderer is stateful\n   122→- `content_block_stop` after text block (no activeTool) must be ignored in tool-complete handler — this is already correctly handled\n   123→- Codepoint-aware truncation for emoji/CJK already implemented in `truncateToWidth()`\n   124→\n   125→### Display Layout Order (top to bottom)\n   126→\n   127→1. **Header** — story key, phase, elapsed, sprint progress\n   128→2. **Story Breakdown** — per-story status with symbols (compact single line)\n   129→3. **Story Messages** — [OK]/[WARN]/[FAIL] messages (permanent, append-only)\n   130→4. **Completed Tools** — ✓ lines (scrolling, max 50)\n   131→5. **Active Tool** — ⚡ with spinner\n   132→6. **Last Thought** — 💭 text\n   133→7. **Retry Notice** — ⏳ (when active)\n   134→\n   135→### What This Story Does NOT Include\n   136→\n   137→- No integration with `run.ts` — that's Story 0.5.4\n   138→- No data sourcing (reading sprint-status.yaml, computing elapsed time) — that's 0.5.4\n   139→- No changes to stream-parser.ts\n   140→- No changes to ralph or bash scripts\n   141→- This story builds the components that CAN render the data; 0.5.4 feeds data in\n   142→\n   143→### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n   144→\n   145→- Do NOT use `console.log` — Ink manages the terminal\n   146→- Do NOT use ANSI escape codes — use Ink's `<Text>` and `<Box>` components\n   147→- Do NOT accumulate ALL text deltas — only keep the LAST thought\n   148→- Do NOT hardcode story data — components receive data via props/state\n   149→- Do NOT break existing tool activity display — enhance, don't replace\n   150→\n   151→### References\n   152→\n   153→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 0.5.3] — original epic ACs\n   154→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-specification.md#Lines 199-252] — live mode display format, story completion messages, status symbols\n   155→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-overhaul.md#Lines 163-197] — journey 1 evening/morning display\n   156→- [Source: src/lib/ink-components.tsx] — existing components to enhance\n   157→- [Source: src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx] — existing controller to enhance\n   158→- [Source: src/lib/stream-parser.ts] — StreamEvent types\n   159→\n   160→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   161→## Verification Requirements\n   162→\n   163→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`verification/0-5-3-ink-terminal-renderer.proof.md`)\n   164→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   165→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   166→\n   167→## Documentation Requirements\n   168→\n   169→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   170→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/0-5-3-ink-terminal-renderer.md`\n   171→\n   172→## Testing Requirements\n   173→\n   174→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   175→- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   176→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   177→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   178→\n   179→## Dev Agent Record\n   180→\n   181→### Agent Model Used\n   182→\n   183→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   184→\n   185→### Debug Log References\n   186→\n   187→### Completion Notes List\n   188→\n   189→- Enhanced existing Ink renderer with 3 new capabilities: elapsed time in header, per-story status breakdown, story completion messages\n   190→- Added `StoryStatusEntry`, `StoryStatusValue`, `StoryMessage` types to ink-components.tsx\n   191→- Added `StoryBreakdown` component — groups stories by status, renders with UX spec symbols (✓/◆/○/✗/✕)\n   192→- Added `StoryMessages` component — renders [OK]/[WARN]/[FAIL] lines with optional detail lines (└ prefix)\n   193→- Expanded `SprintInfo` with optional `elapsed` field, Header renders it when present\n   194→- Expanded `RendererState` with `stories` and `messages` arrays\n   195→- Added `updateStories()` and `addMessage()` to RendererHandle (including no-op handle)\n   196→- 47 vitest tests pass (18 new + 29 existing), 2676 total vitest tests pass, 316 BATS tests pass\n   197→- Both files remain under 300 lines (NFR9): ink-components.tsx=228, ink-renderer.tsx=202\n   198→\n   199→### File List\n   200→\n   201→- src/lib/ink-components.tsx (modified) — added StoryStatusEntry, StoryMessage types; StoryBreakdown, StoryMessages components; expanded SprintInfo and Header; updated App layout\n   202→- src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx (modified) — expanded RendererState; added updateStories(), addMessage() to handle and no-op; re-exported new types\n   203→- src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx (modified) — 18 new tests for header elapsed, StoryBreakdown, StoryMessages, controller methods\n   204→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1eada203-6dd0-4cf1-909a-4daaca264b98","uuid":"abf6b29d-bff1-4cea-a92b-1d52eb4970da","timestamp":"2026-03-20T07:16:43.306Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/codeharness-verify-0-5-3-ink-terminal-renderer/story.md","content":"# Story 0.5.3: Ink Terminal Renderer\n\nStatus: verifying\n\n## Story\n\nAs an operator,\nI want a rich terminal UI built with Ink that shows live Claude activity, per-story progress, session timing, and story completion messages,\nso that I can see at a glance what Claude is doing, how the sprint is progressing, and what happened to each story.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** Claude is executing tools during a run, **When** the operator watches the terminal, **Then** they see the active tool with a spinner (`⚡ [ToolName]`) and each completed tool as a permanent line (`✓ [ToolName] args...`). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n2. **Given** Claude is producing text output, **When** the operator watches the terminal, **Then** they see the latest thought on an updating line (`💭 {text}`), truncated to terminal width. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n3. **Given** a running session, **When** the Ink header renders, **Then** it shows the current story key, phase, elapsed time, and sprint progress — matching the UX spec format: `◆ {story_key} — {phase} | {elapsed} | Sprint: {done}/{total}`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n4. **Given** sprint state data with per-story statuses, **When** the renderer displays the story breakdown section, **Then** it shows stories grouped by status using the UX spec symbols: `✓` done, `◆` in-progress, `○` pending, `✗` failed, `✕` blocked/exhausted — e.g. `Done: 3-1 ✓  4-1 ✓  4-2 ✓ | This: 3-2 ◆ | Next: 3-3 ○`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n5. **Given** a story completes verification successfully, **When** the renderer receives a story-complete event, **Then** it displays `[OK] Story {key}: DONE — {AC count} ACs verified` with duration and cost on a subsequent line. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n6. **Given** a story fails verification, **When** the renderer receives a story-failed event, **Then** it displays `[WARN] Story {key}: verification found {N} failing ACs → returning to dev` with the failing AC details and attempt count. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n7. **Given** an API retry event, **When** rendered, **Then** it shows `⏳ API retry {attempt} (waiting {delay}ms)`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n8. **Given** the `--quiet` flag is set, **When** the renderer is started, **Then** no terminal output is produced — a no-op handle is returned. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n9. **Given** process exit (SIGINT, SIGTERM, or natural end), **When** Ink cleans up, **Then** no orphaned terminal state (cursor, alternate screen buffer) remains. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [x] Task 1: Expand SprintInfo type and Header component (AC: #3)\n  - [x] Add `elapsed?: string` to SprintInfo\n  - [x] Update Header to render elapsed time: `◆ {storyKey} — {phase} | {elapsed} | Sprint: {done}/{total}`\n  - [x] Update tests for new header format\n\n- [x] Task 2: Add per-story status breakdown component (AC: #4)\n  - [x] Define `StoryStatusEntry` type: `{ key: string; status: StoryStatusValue }`\n  - [x] Add `stories: StoryStatusEntry[]` to RendererState\n  - [x] Create `StoryBreakdown` component that groups stories by status and renders with correct symbols (✓/◆/○/✗/✕)\n  - [x] Add `updateStories(stories: StoryStatusEntry[])` to RendererHandle\n  - [x] Compact single-line format: `Done: 3-1 ✓  4-1 ✓ | This: 3-2 ◆ | Next: 3-3 ○`\n  - [x] Update tests\n\n- [x] Task 3: Add story completion/failure message components (AC: #5, #6)\n  - [x] Define `StoryMessage` type: `{ type: 'ok' | 'warn' | 'fail'; key: string; message: string; details?: string[] }`\n  - [x] Add `messages: StoryMessage[]` to RendererState\n  - [x] Create `StoryMessages` component rendering `[OK]`/`[WARN]`/`[FAIL]` lines per UX spec format\n  - [x] Add `addMessage(msg: StoryMessage)` to RendererHandle\n  - [x] Messages are permanent (append-only, not overwritten)\n  - [x] Update tests\n\n- [x] Task 4: Wire new components into App and renderer controller (AC: #1-#9)\n  - [x] Add StoryBreakdown and StoryMessages to App component tree\n  - [x] Expose new methods on RendererHandle: `updateStories()`, `addMessage()`\n  - [x] Ensure no-op handle includes new methods\n  - [x] Verify signal handling still works with expanded state\n\n- [x] Task 5: Update tests for all new/changed behavior (AC: #1-#9)\n  - [x] Test Header renders elapsed time\n  - [x] Test StoryBreakdown renders correct symbols per status\n  - [x] Test StoryMessages renders [OK], [WARN], [FAIL] formats\n  - [x] Test updateStories() and addMessage() on RendererHandle\n  - [x] Test no-op handle includes new methods\n  - [x] All 29 existing tests still pass (47 total now)\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### What Exists (Enhance, Don't Rewrite)\n\nThe Ink renderer already works for tool activity display. This story ENHANCES it with:\n1. Richer header (add elapsed time)\n2. Per-story status section (new component)\n3. Story completion messages (new component)\n\n**Do NOT rewrite ink-components.tsx or ink-renderer.tsx from scratch.** Add new components and expand existing types. The existing tool activity display (⚡ spinner, ✓ completed, 💭 thought, ⏳ retry) is correct and should not change.\n\n### Key Files to Modify\n\n- `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` — Add StoryBreakdown, StoryMessages components; expand SprintInfo type; update Header; update App\n- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` — Expand RendererState; add updateStories(), addMessage() to handle; update no-op handle\n- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` — Add tests for new components and API\n\n### Key Files to Read (Do NOT Modify)\n\n- `src/lib/stream-parser.ts` — StreamEvent types consumed by the renderer\n- `src/commands/run.ts` — Where the renderer is integrated (modified in 0.5.4, not this story)\n\n### Architecture Constraints\n\n- **NFR9: No file > 300 lines.** If ink-components.tsx exceeds 300 lines after adding new components, split into `ink-components.tsx` (existing) and `ink-status-components.tsx` (new story/status components).\n- **Vitest** for unit tests, **100% coverage target**\n- **ink-testing-library** for component rendering tests (already a devDependency)\n- **TSX** with `\"jsx\": \"react-jsx\"` in tsconfig (already configured)\n\n### UX Spec Reference — Expected Visual Output\n\nThe live mode display should look like this (from UX spec):\n\n```\n◆ 3-2-bmad-installation-workflow-patching — verify | 47m | Sprint: 18/65\nDone: 3-1 ✓  4-1 ✓  4-2 ✓\nThis: 3-2 ◆ verifying\nNext: 3-3 ○\n\n✓ [Bash] npm run test:unit 2>&1 | tail -20\n✓ [Read] src/modules/sprint/state.ts\n⚡ [Bash] docker exec codeharness-verify ...\n💭 Running the verification container to check AC 8...\n```\n\nStory completion messages (displayed between stories):\n```\n[OK] Story 3-2: DONE — 12/12 ACs verified (18m, $4.20)\n[WARN] Story 3-3: verification found 2 failing ACs → returning to dev (attempt 2/10)\n```\n\n### Previous Story Intelligence (0.5.2)\n\n- Parser is stateless per-line; renderer is stateful\n- `content_block_stop` after text block (no activeTool) must be ignored in tool-complete handler — this is already correctly handled\n- Codepoint-aware truncation for emoji/CJK already implemented in `truncateToWidth()`\n\n### Display Layout Order (top to bottom)\n\n1. **Header** — story key, phase, elapsed, sprint progress\n2. **Story Breakdown** — per-story status with symbols (compact single line)\n3. **Story Messages** — [OK]/[WARN]/[FAIL] messages (permanent, append-only)\n4. **Completed Tools** — ✓ lines (scrolling, max 50)\n5. **Active Tool** — ⚡ with spinner\n6. **Last Thought** — 💭 text\n7. **Retry Notice** — ⏳ (when active)\n\n### What This Story Does NOT Include\n\n- No integration with `run.ts` — that's Story 0.5.4\n- No data sourcing (reading sprint-status.yaml, computing elapsed time) — that's 0.5.4\n- No changes to stream-parser.ts\n- No changes to ralph or bash scripts\n- This story builds the components that CAN render the data; 0.5.4 feeds data in\n\n### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n\n- Do NOT use `console.log` — Ink manages the terminal\n- Do NOT use ANSI escape codes — use Ink's `<Text>` and `<Box>` components\n- Do NOT accumulate ALL text deltas — only keep the LAST thought\n- Do NOT hardcode story data — components receive data via props/state\n- Do NOT break existing tool activity display — enhance, don't replace\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 0.5.3] — original epic ACs\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-specification.md#Lines 199-252] — live mode display format, story completion messages, status symbols\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-overhaul.md#Lines 163-197] — journey 1 evening/morning display\n- [Source: src/lib/ink-components.tsx] — existing components to enhance\n- [Source: src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx] — existing controller to enhance\n- [Source: src/lib/stream-parser.ts] — StreamEvent types\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`verification/0-5-3-ink-terminal-renderer.proof.md`)\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/0-5-3-ink-terminal-renderer.md`\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n\n## Dev Agent Record\n\n### Agent Model Used\n\nClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n\n### Debug Log References\n\n### Completion Notes List\n\n- Enhanced existing Ink renderer with 3 new capabilities: elapsed time in header, per-story status breakdown, story completion messages\n- Added `StoryStatusEntry`, `StoryStatusValue`, `StoryMessage` types to ink-components.tsx\n- Added `StoryBreakdown` component — groups stories by status, renders with UX spec symbols (✓/◆/○/✗/✕)\n- Added `StoryMessages` component — renders [OK]/[WARN]/[FAIL] lines with optional detail lines (└ prefix)\n- Expanded `SprintInfo` with optional `elapsed` field, Header renders it when present\n- Expanded `RendererState` with `stories` and `messages` arrays\n- Added `updateStories()` and `addMessage()` to RendererHandle (including no-op handle)\n- 47 vitest tests pass (18 new + 29 existing), 2676 total vitest tests pass, 316 BATS tests pass\n- Both files remain under 300 lines (NFR9): ink-components.tsx=228, ink-renderer.tsx=202\n\n### File List\n\n- src/lib/ink-components.tsx (modified) — added StoryStatusEntry, StoryMessage types; StoryBreakdown, StoryMessages components; expanded SprintInfo and Header; updated App layout\n- src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx (modified) — expanded RendererState; added updateStories(), addMessage() to handle and no-op; re-exported new types\n- src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx (modified) — 18 new tests for header elapsed, StoryBreakdown, StoryMessages, controller methods\n","numLines":204,"startLine":1,"totalLines":204}}}
