{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XtE2EiW5kvNzb8RhkJvS11","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a UI component story. The ACs are about Ink components rendering specific formats. The key challenge for black-box verification is that these are React/Ink components — they're not directly CLI commands. The story explicitly says \"No integration with run.ts — that's Story 0.5.4\" and \"This story builds the components that CAN render the data; 0.5.4 feeds data in\".\n\nSo the Docker container won't have a way to exercise these components via CLI because they're internal UI building blocks, not CLI commands. The verifier will need to run the tests inside the container or use node to import and test the components.\n\nActually wait — the container has `node` and the built dist/. But dist/ may not export the ink components since they're internal library code, not CLI entry points.\n\n\nThe verifier could try importing the components directly through node_modules or using `node -e` to test specific imports, though it's unclear if the public API exposes these internal components. I'll run the verifier and see what's actually possible — if the components aren't accessible, we'll need to handle that case.\n\nSince there's no unit-test tag and the story has no CLI surface to exercise, I need to proceed with black-box verification. I'll construct a prompt that attempts to import and render these components through docker exec commands.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4155,"cache_read_input_tokens":59717,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4155},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1eada203-6dd0-4cf1-909a-4daaca264b98","uuid":"0c7cab31-a58e-4a8e-be44-388952878961"}
