{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XtE2EiW5kvNzb8RhkJvS11","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Q7A4E8BtWPfmMEY3C49jbt","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /tmp/codeharness-verify-0-5-3-ink-terminal-renderer && claude --print --max-budget-usd 5 --allowedTools Bash Read Write Glob Grep Edit -p \"You are a black-box verifier. Your job is to verify that a software feature works correctly from the user's perspective — using ONLY the installed CLI, documentation, and observability data. You have NO access to source code.\n\n## Why Black-Box Verification\n\nThis workspace contains NO source code. The \\`src/\\` directory does not exist. This is intentional — you must verify the feature works as a user would experience it, not by reading implementation details. If you cannot verify a feature from docs + CLI alone, that is a REAL failure in the product's documentation or packaging.\n\n## Step 1: Read README.md\n\nStart by reading \\`README.md\\` in this workspace. It contains install and usage instructions for the project. Use it to understand how to exercise the CLI.\n\n## Step 2: Review Acceptance Criteria\n\nThe story file \\`story.md\\` contains the acceptance criteria you must verify. Read it now.\n\n## Step 3: Verify Each AC\n\nFor EACH acceptance criterion, you must:\n\n1. Run commands inside the Docker container via \\`docker exec codeharness-verify ...\\`\n2. Capture the command output as evidence\n3. Query observability endpoints if runtime evidence is needed\n\n### Docker Container\n\n- Container name: \\`codeharness-verify\\`\n- ALL CLI commands MUST run via: \\`docker exec codeharness-verify <command>\\`\n- Example: \\`docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness --version\\`\n\n### Project Type: Node.js CLI\n\nExecute commands inside the container and capture stdout/stderr as evidence:\n- \\`docker exec codeharness-verify <cli-command> [args]\\`\n- Capture exit codes: \\`docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c '<command>; echo \\\"EXIT:\\$?\\\"'\\`\n- For Node.js projects, the built artifact is installed globally in the container.\n\n### IMPORTANT CONTEXT FOR THIS STORY\n\nThis story (0.5.3) is about **internal Ink/React UI components** — NOT CLI commands. The components are:\n- Header (renders story key, phase, elapsed, sprint progress)\n- StoryBreakdown (renders per-story status with symbols)\n- StoryMessages (renders [OK]/[WARN]/[FAIL] lines)\n- Tool activity display (spinner, completed tools, thoughts, retry)\n\nThese components are exported from the npm package's internal modules. To verify them, use \\`node -e\\` inside the container to:\n1. Import the renderer module: \\`require('codeharness/dist/index.js')\\` or find where the exports live\n2. Check that exported types and functions exist\n3. Run the unit tests if available: \\`docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness && ls'\\`\n\nSince these are React/Ink components, full rendering requires a TTY. Focus on verifying:\n- The exports exist and have correct types\n- The createRenderer function works with quiet mode (returns no-op handle)\n- The RendererHandle has the expected methods\n\n### Observability Endpoints\n\nQuery these from the HOST (not inside the container) for runtime evidence:\n- **VictoriaLogs**: \\`http://localhost:9428\\`\n- **VictoriaMetrics**: \\`http://localhost:8428\\`\n\n## Step 4: Write Proof Document\n\nWrite your verification proof to: \\`verification/0-5-3-ink-terminal-renderer-proof.md\\`\n\nUse this format for each AC:\n\n\\`\\`\\`markdown\n## AC N: <description>\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify <command>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n\\`\\`\\`output\n<actual output>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**IMPORTANT: Only use \\`bash\\` and \\`output\\` as code fence languages.** Never use bare fences without a language tag.\n\n## Critical Rules\n\n1. **ALL commands MUST use \\`docker exec codeharness-verify ...\\`** — do NOT run commands directly on the host filesystem.\n2. **Do NOT attempt to access source code** — there is no \\`src/\\` directory in this workspace.\n3. **Report REAL failures** — if a feature does not work, report that as a verification failure. Do NOT fabricate passing evidence.\n4. **Every AC needs functional evidence** — reading docs alone is not evidence. Execute commands and capture output.\n5. **[ESCALATE] is ONLY for things genuinely impossible to automate** — NOT for infrastructure problems.\n6. **Never switch to unit-testable verification.** Report failures as [FAIL].\n\" 2>&1","description":"Run black-box verifier session for 0-5-3","timeout":300000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4155,"cache_read_input_tokens":59717,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4155},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1eada203-6dd0-4cf1-909a-4daaca264b98","uuid":"04e2e603-3a3c-42d3-a1f7-9f4a304fbb7e"}
